    assessmentFindings: ["Injection site reactions: localized erythema, swelling, and tenderness (expected and self-limiting)","Low-grade fever and malaise within 24-48 hours post-vaccination (common systemic response)","Lymphadenopathy ipsilateral to injection site (particularly with COVID-19 mRNA vaccines and Shingrix)","Allergic reactions: urticaria, pruritus at or beyond injection site (mild to moderate)","Syncope or pre-syncopal symptoms (vasovagal reaction, more common in adolescents and young adults)","History of prior vaccine reactions guiding future vaccine selection and precautions","Assessment of immune status to determine safe vaccine types (live vs. inactivated)"],
